node.text:
Wrote a new song lately‚Ä¶

Everybody have different experiences in life, some grew up in a fish tank thinking it was an ocean. I grew up in an ocean thinking it was a tank. So how can two people with different mind sets understand each other? But I have to grow up now, and say no to creatures that don‚Äôt belong in my reef. Was never good at expressing or speaking up for myself so I wrote it in a song. 

Here‚Äôs a titbit of it üòâ

node.text: The epitome of practice! I couldn‚Äôt get a single note the first day!!! This is my fourth day!!! I DID IT WAHAHAHAHA!! GET TO PLAY MY FAV SONG! üòçüòù‚úåüèª #fender

Sun kissed skin üíõ

This year I lost a lot of confidence and a lot of bumps on the road. This trip was exactly what I needed and a great way to kick off my 2023. 
I used to be severely underweight, and people would always say wow you‚Äôre so beautiful, so pretty, I wasn‚Äôt starving myself, but I always felt like I need to to keep my body the way it is. But now I‚Äôm just healthy, I eat, a little too much sometimes hahahhaha, but I‚Äôm happy! That‚Äôs so much more important.
On my way to hua hin! üõ∂‚úåüèª

Today at Chatchuchak Market, the shop owner said I looked familiar and asked if I was Eleanor. Omg‚Ä¶ she actually watched most of my shows! I can‚Äôt believe I have a Thailand fan! üòù‚úåüèªso honored and happy that my projects are being recognized all over!!! What a great start to my 2023! üíõ

And yes, pic three is me asking my mom if I can buy them. ü•π

I know orchids are Singapore‚Äôs flower but hear me out. So I can‚Äôt help but laugh sometimes when I see a white orchid, because when I was a new student in my high school, about three days of entering this new school, I had a secret admirer who sends me secret admirer roses that my school does on valentines, and sends me a lot of well wishing cards with lovely poems on every festivity. It was my first time experiencing something like that, I was always that weird awkward and laugh-so-loud kind of girl, I just had my braces taken off before going into this school. So‚Ä¶ I kinda had a whole new reputation. A good one, people thought I was pretty!!! üòÇ So after about a few months‚Ä¶ one day, someone tapped on my shoulder as our classes were making our way to lunch in the hallways, as I turned my head, I couldn‚Äôt see anyone, then I slowly looked down to see a young boy who was about five foot tall, giving me an orchid just to reveal himself as my admirer and ran away. Yes he ‚Äúran away‚Äù. OMG. My secret admirer was a fetus. 
And here I thought I was living the teenage dream. ü•πüòÇ

I don‚Äôt do these long cringey captions often, but‚Ä¶ I have a lot of thoughts I‚Äôd like to share.
As a new year arrives, I tend to think I‚Äôve learned a lot and I will say: it‚Äôll get better NEXT YEAR. I mean it‚Äôs good right? To think positively. But every time I tell myself to learn something, I usually only really learn the true meaning of it AFTER the whole year has already passed hahahaha. I guess this is what it‚Äôs like growing up? Learning from your mistakes and experiences. I‚Äôm still learning so much about life itself, a lot about myself.

I‚Äôm still learning how to be confident, secure and be 100% myself. I usually hide behind this fa√ßade and act like I‚Äôm always doing GREAT. But the truth is, I get anxious, i get super insecure, I‚Äôm not social cause I‚Äôm shy, I get upset and I get frustrated. ALOT. I like to put myself down. ALOT. 
I tend to talk myself down so much until I really believe it, and slowly I lose myself in this endless dark pit. Then each year, I slowly pick myself back up again. I guess, always searching for meaning in life, fighting for yourself, is the meaning of life itself. 

But I have to remember‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm young & I still have time to grow. Manifesting great things this year. I also want to thank so many people who have been with me, left me, loved me, supported me in my journey of growth. 
Maybe this year my motto should be: what would Taylor swift do. üòÜüíï
